 ….Tells Diaspora Nigerians to use their resources develop Nigeria
By Johnbosco Agbakwuru President Buhari on Friday said that he was shocked over the attacks on Nigerians in South Africa. He described the attacks of foreign nationals in the country as an embarrassment to the African continent. President Buhari who stated this in Pretoria, when he met with Nigerians in the Diaspora in South Africa, advised them to always remember their country with skills, resources and talents, and work towards living decent and dignified lives that bring honour to their fatherland. Continue reading Xenophobia: I was shocked on attacks on Nigerians ―Buhari at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard